commitResults.messageBody:
To display appointments in the GUI, let's add AppointmentCard and
AppointmentListpanel, which handles the display of appointments
onto JavaFX.

To store Appointments into SuperSalon, let's create Manager classes
to store appointments into a UniqueList.

To manipulate Appointments stored in the Model, ModelManager must contain
an AppointmentManager. Let's add methods into ModelManager to handle
Appointments.

Added command to add appointment and edited Model classes to include
Appointment Manager.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Appointment, Add Parser for AddAppointmentCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
AddAppointmentCommandParser will create a Command containing an Appointment object.
The command will be executed to store into the model and storage.

However, it is not possible to create Client and Service objects within ParserUtil as attributes
for Appointment, as a search is needed to be performed within Model to match the input Phone
and input ServiceCode to the right Client and Service. Thus, let's refactor Appointment to
include Phone and ServiceCode as attributes, while making Client and Service Optional.
Added methods to include Appointments

Service list is currently an implementation of a generic Unique List.
To find a service by service code, we need to overload the contains
method to accept a service code. Let's create a unique service class
to contain this method.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Duration attribute and parse method

commitResults.messageBody:
ServiceCode can take a maximum of 1000 unique codes from SC000-999.
Codes are not recycled, even when a Service is deleted. We feel that
having an allowance of 1000 unique service codes is sufficient for any
home-based beauty salon to store the list of all their services.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add more functionality to Service class

commitResults.messageBody:
A UniqueList represents a list that contains unique items. Similar to
AB3's ClientList, however UniqueList utilizes Java generics for it to be
extensible to further functionalities that also requires a UniqueList.

commitResults.messageBody:
ServiceCode generation will look at all the current Services and create
a service code ranging from SC000-999 that is not yet used in the
current list of Services. This allows for ServiceCodes to be recyclable,
allowing users to make use of the entire 1000 possible ServiceCodes.
